text: Chewawah Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Cane Creek. Scholarly opinions are divided whether the name Chewawah is derived from the Chickasaw language meaning "cedar", or is a corruption of the name of the Mexican state of Chihuahua. Variant names are "Chemew Creek" and "Sawaha Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Chickasaw County, Mississippi
